The paper discusses the limitations of heuristic algorithms on NP-hard problems, which is a topic closely related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions deterministic heuristics for randomized computation (cs.AI) and the effectiveness of heuristics in practice (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper touches on the analysis of algorithms (cs.DM) in terms of their success rates.
